\c 20
\cl John 20
\cd Christ's resurrection, and manifestation to his disciples.
\p
\v 1 And *on the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene cometh in the morning, it being yet dark, to the sepulchre; and she saw the stone taken away from the sepulchre.
\p
\v 2 She ran, therefore, and cometh to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple whom Jesus loved, and saith to them; They have taken away the Lord out of the sepulchre, and we know not where they have laid him.
\p
\v 3 Peter, therefore, went out, and that other disciple, and they came to the sepulchre.
\p
\v 4 And they both ran together, and that other disciple out-ran Peter, and came first to the sepulchre.
\p
\v 5 And when he stooped down, he saw the linen cloths lying; but yet he went not in.
\p
\v 6 Then cometh Simon Peter, following him, and went into the sepulchre, and saw the linen cloths lying,
\p
\v 7 And the napkin, that had been about his head, not lying with the linen cloths, but apart, wrapt up into one place.
\p
\v 8 Then that other disciple also went in, who came first to the sepulchre; and he saw, and believed.
\p
\v 9 For as yet they knew not the Scripture, that he must rise again from the dead.
\p
\v 10 The disciples therefore went away again to their home.
\p
\v 11 *But Mary stood without at the sepulchre, weeping. Whilst she was then weeping, she stooped down, and looked into the sepulchre:
\p
\v 12 And she saw two Angels in white, sitting, one at the head, and one at the feet, where the body of Jesus had been laid.
\p
\v 13 They say to her; Woman, why weepest thou? She saith to them; Because they have taken away my Lord, and I know not where they have laid him.
\p
\v 14 When she had said this, she turned herself back, and saw Jesus standing: and she knew not that it was Jesus.
\p
\v 15 Jesus saith to her; Woman, why weepest thou? whom seekest thou? She thinking that it was the gardener, saith to him; Sir, if thou hast taken him away, tell me where thou hast laid him: and I will take him away.
\p
\v 16 Jesus saith to her; Mary. She turning, saith to him; Rabboni, (that is to say, Master).
\p
\v 17 Jesus saith to her; Do not touch me, for I have not yet ascended to my Father: but go to my brethren, and say to them; I ascend to my Father and to your Father, to my God and your God.
\p
\v 18 Mary Magdalene cometh, and telleth the disciples; I have seen the Lord, and these things he said to me.
\p
\v 19 *Now when it was late that same day, the first of the week, and the doors were shut, where the disciples were gathered together for fear of the Jews: Jesus came and stood in the midst, and said to them; Peace be to you.
\p
\v 20 And when he had said this, he shewed them his hands, and his side. The disciples, therefore, were glad, when they saw the Lord.
\p
\v 21 He said therefore to them again; Peace be to you. As the Father hath sent me, I also send you.
\p
\v 22 When he had said this, he breathed on them, and he said to them: Receive ye the Holy Ghost:
\p
\v 23 *Whose sins you shall forgive, they are forgiven them: and whose you shall retain, they are retained.
\p
\v 24 Now Thomas, one of the twelve, who is called Didymus, was not with them when Jesus came.
\p
\v 25 The other disciples, therefore, said to him; We have seen the Lord. But he said to them; Unless I shall see in his hands the print of the nails, and put my finger into the place of the nails, and put my hand into his side, I will not believe.
\p
\v 26 And after eight days, his disciples were again within, and Thomas with them. Jesus cometh, the doors being shut, and stood in the midst, and said; Peace be to you.
\p
\v 27 Then he saith to Thomas; Put in thy finger hither, and see my hands, and bring hither thy hand, and put it into my side: and be not incredulous, but faithful.
\p
\v 28 Thomas answered, and said to him; My Lord, and my God.
\p
\v 29 Jesus saith to him; Because thou hast seen me, Thomas, thou hast believed: blessed are they that have not seen, and have believed.
\p
\v 30 *Many other signs also did Jesus in the sight of his disciples, which are not written in this book.
\p
\v 31 But these are written that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God: and that believing you may have life in his name.
